WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.250
[pages riffling]

00:08.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:14.000
♪

00:19.500 --> 00:22.417
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

00:22.917 --> 00:24.292
‐ Good morning!

00:26.625 --> 00:28.167
Who wants breakfast?

00:29.458 --> 00:31.417
Hi. Hi!

00:31.417 --> 00:33.000
Oh, who's hungry?

00:34.375 --> 00:36.042
[bellows]

00:37.292 --> 00:40.375
Hi, hi.
[tiger growls]

00:46.125 --> 00:48.542
Morning, troops!
Breakfast ti‐‐

00:48.542 --> 00:51.250
Ah!
[screams]

00:53.625 --> 00:58.083
♪

01:01.750 --> 01:05.333
♪

01:08.833 --> 01:12.583
♪

01:18.792 --> 01:21.458
BRYCE: Look,
the list is absurd, okay.

01:21.458 --> 01:25.083
[stammers] It started with a, um,
a psychotic Fish Lady

01:25.083 --> 01:27.458
and just got crazier
from there, right? Okay?

01:27.458 --> 01:30.625
You know, we had the, um,
there was the Marlon Brando wannabe

01:30.625 --> 01:31.958
in the bottom
of the prison, right?

01:31.958 --> 01:35.125
And uh, uh, yeah, the General,
the Fish Lady's kids,

01:35.125 --> 01:36.250
the weird rockabillies.

01:36.250 --> 01:38.375
Oh‐oh, hey, come on,
what about the Poacher?

01:38.375 --> 01:41.750
And oh, let's not forget
about The Rooster, right?

01:41.750 --> 01:44.542
And his 50 goddamn doubles.

01:44.542 --> 01:46.167
Look. Point is, you said

01:46.167 --> 01:49.208
if we "ripped the seeds
of evil from the ground,"

01:49.208 --> 01:51.125
I get to ascend. Alright?

01:51.125 --> 01:53.250
[Monkey grunts]
That's your words!

01:53.250 --> 01:56.125
Well, all is ripped
and yet here I am, man,

01:56.125 --> 01:58.792
still stuck in monkey purgatory!

02:00.625 --> 02:03.958
Will you please stop snacking?

02:03.958 --> 02:04.917
[Ryoshin clears throat]

02:08.083 --> 02:09.875
[breathes deeply]

02:11.167 --> 02:13.458
Oh, for shit's sake,
will you say something?

02:14.083 --> 02:15.292
[sighs deeply]

02:17.042 --> 02:17.958
‐ Come.

02:21.208 --> 02:23.583
‐ Oh yay. A garden tour.

02:23.583 --> 02:26.375
Hey, look, there's a hedge.
Ooh, ooh, and another hedge.

02:26.375 --> 02:28.125
Oh my god,
there are some rocks.

02:28.125 --> 02:30.500
Oh‐ho, wow.
I mean, so round.

02:30.500 --> 02:32.250
You know,
I love looking at rocks

02:32.250 --> 02:33.792
and not getting answers
to my questio‐‐

02:33.792 --> 02:34.750
Oof!

02:35.458 --> 02:36.708
What the hell?

02:36.708 --> 02:39.750
Hey. Hey, guys.
Guys, I think the garden is broken.

02:40.333 --> 02:42.000
Ow! What the shit?

02:42.000 --> 02:43.917
[hooting]

02:43.917 --> 02:44.583
‐ Salt.

02:45.208 --> 02:47.500
Shinto use it
to ward off demons.

02:47.917 --> 02:50.167
‐ Uh, I‐I'm sorry, what is this,
some sorta weird test?

02:50.167 --> 02:51.500
Ah, shit!

02:51.500 --> 02:53.333
Oh, that's not a test!

02:53.333 --> 02:55.292
[whimpers]
‐ That's right.

02:55.292 --> 02:58.625
Demons are talkative,
arrogant, and entitled.

02:59.292 --> 03:01.375
But in his case,
he may just be American.

03:01.375 --> 03:03.125
[Monkey growls]
Hard to tell.

03:03.458 --> 03:05.833
‐ Hey! Damn it!
Hey, Monkey, come on,

03:05.833 --> 03:07.625
lend me a... a paw!

03:08.250 --> 03:10.458
Actually, hold on. Uh, hold‐‐
hold that thought‐‐

03:10.458 --> 03:12.792
[retches, groans]

03:13.917 --> 03:15.792
[coughs, retches]

03:16.292 --> 03:19.375
‐ Either way,
he is beholden to you,

03:19.833 --> 03:21.000
not the other way around.

03:21.708 --> 03:24.083
Yes. It is you
who must lead the way.

03:24.500 --> 03:27.875
But be wary, for you travel
the same path

03:27.875 --> 03:29.708
yet risk walking alone.

03:30.500 --> 03:32.542
Now here, have a cracker.

03:36.250 --> 03:38.042
‐ Augh, Okay, good.

03:38.042 --> 03:40.375
[coughing]

03:40.917 --> 03:42.375
[groans]

03:42.375 --> 03:44.667
Oh wow. Peaks and valleys.

03:46.208 --> 03:48.958
HARUKA:
Chopsticks, nails, toothpicks.

03:49.417 --> 03:52.292
Looks like our suspect has a thing
for everyday household items.

03:52.292 --> 03:54.458
‐ Took his time
with each one, too.

03:55.000 --> 03:56.375
Poor bastards.

03:57.333 --> 03:58.917
‐ You think it's connected
to our Monkey?

03:58.917 --> 04:01.292
‐ Hmm. Hard to see
how it couldn't be.
[squelching]

04:01.625 --> 04:03.458
‐ Oh, gross. Ew.

04:06.917 --> 04:08.000
‐ What you got there?

04:08.500 --> 04:10.250
‐ It's‐‐
ZOOKEEPER: Persimmons.

04:10.250 --> 04:14.000
They used to take one bite,
then toss the rest.

04:14.000 --> 04:15.875
It used
to drive me crazy.

04:16.417 --> 04:18.083
[Zookeeper crying]

04:20.917 --> 04:21.917
ITO: Haruka,

04:22.542 --> 04:23.542
what is it?

04:24.583 --> 04:25.917
‐ I've seen this before.

04:28.375 --> 04:31.417
[Bryce groaning, coughing]

04:31.958 --> 04:34.875
‐ Hey, never trust a man
in a robe, alright?

04:35.208 --> 04:37.833
[retching, coughing]

04:37.833 --> 04:38.958
Oh god.

04:38.958 --> 04:40.375
Oh, I hope
I don't need those.

04:40.625 --> 04:41.542
No‐‐

04:42.917 --> 04:45.750
♪ foreboding music playing ♪

04:45.750 --> 04:47.375
[crowd gasps]

04:48.417 --> 04:51.375
What are you‐‐
What are you looking at? What‐‐

04:51.708 --> 04:52.750
Oh.

04:52.750 --> 04:54.750
A target with two rings.

04:55.292 --> 04:57.000
I‐I know that calling card.

04:57.000 --> 04:58.542
Hey, Monkey, we gotta go.

04:58.542 --> 04:59.583
[Monkey screeching]

04:59.583 --> 05:01.000
I'll explain on the way.
Come on.

05:01.000 --> 05:02.333
We gotta go get
our guns, now!

05:07.542 --> 05:09.458
‐ Yeah, Let's make sure
we canvass Sanchomé

05:09.458 --> 05:11.792
and get 50 more posters printed.

05:11.792 --> 05:14.000
Now, the tag should read,

05:14.000 --> 05:16.458
"In Shinji We Trust."

05:16.458 --> 05:19.042
Not "In Shinji We Thrust."

05:19.875 --> 05:21.500
No, no, it said "Thrust."

05:22.042 --> 05:23.208
Just make it right.

05:24.208 --> 05:25.208
Gentlemen?

05:26.625 --> 05:27.542
Hello?

05:28.625 --> 05:29.667
Guys?

05:31.708 --> 05:33.375
I'm sorry.
Did you say "fired"?

05:33.792 --> 05:37.542
‐ Donors are threatening
to pull funding if I don't do this.

05:37.542 --> 05:40.333
‐ I can fix this.
‐ We're down six points.

05:40.333 --> 05:41.625
‐ That's just a temporary‐‐

05:41.625 --> 05:46.292
‐ And Ozu is up ten
on trustworthiness.

05:47.250 --> 05:48.333
[sighs]

05:48.708 --> 05:51.875
Accusing Ozu of Ken's death
is one thing,

05:51.875 --> 05:54.875
but defending
some murderous monkey?

05:55.292 --> 05:58.292
Did you even think
about how that would make us look?

05:58.292 --> 06:01.875
‐ At Ken's funeral,
that monkey saved my life,

06:01.875 --> 06:02.917
and yours.

06:02.917 --> 06:04.583
‐ How can you be so sure?

06:05.083 --> 06:07.167
He was carrying a gun,
wasn't he?

06:07.917 --> 06:10.500
How do you know he wasn't there
to kill someone?

06:10.500 --> 06:13.000
Another hit
on his damn list.

06:15.167 --> 06:17.250
‐ Uncle, please.

06:17.250 --> 06:18.667
‐ I'm sorry, Akiko.

06:19.708 --> 06:21.458
It's already done.

06:26.042 --> 06:30.500
♪

06:37.208 --> 06:40.542
♪

06:44.833 --> 06:46.917
‐ Okay, so look,
there were only two things

06:46.917 --> 06:49.083
that scared me in this world
when I was alive.

06:49.083 --> 06:52.208
One: ghosts, which is
pretty damn ironic right now.

06:52.208 --> 06:54.333
The other one:
Lady Bullseye. Alright?

06:55.083 --> 06:57.792
[Monkey hoots]
Dude, you have no idea, alright?

06:57.792 --> 07:00.417
I‐I mean, this isn't
the Poacher, okay.

07:00.667 --> 07:03.292
Lady Bullseye is
on a different level.

07:03.292 --> 07:06.667
She's, uh, Hannibal Lecter
and Rambo in super tight pants.

07:06.667 --> 07:09.750
And she's gonna come after you,
and she's going to come after Akiko,

07:09.750 --> 07:11.458
after this stupid cat.

07:11.458 --> 07:12.208
[growls]

07:12.208 --> 07:14.750
I mean, she'll kill
the whole neighborhood, you know.

07:14.750 --> 07:17.292
Just because she's in a bad mood.
I mean, or a good mood.

07:17.292 --> 07:18.292
Doesn't matter.

07:18.292 --> 07:19.917
[door lock rattling]
Holy shit!

07:22.417 --> 07:23.917
Shoot! Shoot! Shoot her!

07:23.917 --> 07:25.208
Shoot her! That's her!

07:26.458 --> 07:27.667
‐ Oh my god!

07:28.167 --> 07:29.958
What the hell is this?

07:29.958 --> 07:32.125
[growling]

07:32.125 --> 07:34.750
Monkey!
‐ Dude, we do not have time for this.

07:34.750 --> 07:36.708
‐ Explain.
[Monkey hooting]

07:39.417 --> 07:40.917
‐ Hey, she doesn't
speak Monkey, Monkey.

07:40.917 --> 07:43.042
‐ Oh my god, I don't know
what you're saying.

07:43.042 --> 07:43.625
‐ See what I mean?

07:43.625 --> 07:46.083
‐ It's guns like these
that killed Ken Takahara!

07:46.875 --> 07:49.042
‐ Actually it was a, uh,
modified Barrett M95,

07:49.042 --> 07:51.458
but hey, who cares
about details, I'll be over here.

07:51.458 --> 07:53.917
No worries.
[Monkey grunts, hoots]

07:53.917 --> 07:55.625
AKIKO: I, I don't‐‐ I‐‐

07:55.625 --> 07:57.167
What?
[Monkey growls]

07:57.167 --> 07:58.667
[hooting]
Just stop!

07:59.042 --> 08:00.792
I can't deal
with this right now.

08:01.458 --> 08:03.708
Augh... I need you
to leave.

08:03.708 --> 08:06.167
[whines]

08:06.167 --> 08:08.958
‐ Hey, uh, Monkey, bud,
we got company.

08:09.667 --> 08:10.958
‐ Haruka, slow down.

08:11.333 --> 08:12.792
We need a game plan.

08:12.792 --> 08:14.125
‐ A game plan?

08:14.125 --> 08:16.417
If the monkey is there,
we arrest it.

08:16.417 --> 08:18.583
‐ I'm not so sure
that's the play here.

08:18.583 --> 08:20.750
‐ Oh my god,
you always want to wait!

08:20.750 --> 08:23.042
Why can't we just go
in there and‐‐

08:23.042 --> 08:24.792
Oh shit.
‐ Huh?

08:27.792 --> 08:28.833
‐ Hey there.

08:29.750 --> 08:31.500
‐ Oh, we are so screwed.

08:31.500 --> 08:33.250
[meows]

08:33.250 --> 08:34.708
‐ Bye‐bye.
[click]

08:34.708 --> 08:35.542
‐ Get down!

08:50.750 --> 08:53.458
[whines]

08:54.875 --> 08:55.833
BRYCE: [muffled voice] Monkey!

08:56.542 --> 08:59.042
Monkey! Monkey!

08:59.500 --> 09:02.292
Hey, don't just lie there!
Let's go! Run!

09:03.083 --> 09:04.250
Come on, man, get up!

09:05.958 --> 09:08.458
Run!
[screeching]

09:08.458 --> 09:10.333
Not towards the danger!

09:17.542 --> 09:19.750
Hey‐hey, listen, if we keep
that psychopath here,

09:19.750 --> 09:21.542
anything that isn't dead yet
will be.

09:21.542 --> 09:23.500
So if you want
to save Akiko,

09:23.500 --> 09:24.958
you gotta get
the hell outta here!

09:28.667 --> 09:29.500
[Lady Bullseye yells]

09:30.875 --> 09:31.875
Monkey!

09:31.875 --> 09:34.833
♪ tense music playing ♪

09:34.833 --> 09:37.708
♪

09:41.042 --> 09:42.208
[growls]

09:44.583 --> 09:47.208
‐ Is this really
what my career has come to?

09:47.208 --> 09:49.125
Killing circus animals?

09:50.208 --> 09:54.083
But that's why I gotta remind myself
why I got into this business.

09:54.583 --> 09:57.917
Because I genuinely love
to torture.

09:57.917 --> 10:00.208
[hooting]

10:00.833 --> 10:01.875
HARUKA: Freeze!

10:02.875 --> 10:03.667
On the ground.

10:04.333 --> 10:05.167
Now.

10:05.167 --> 10:07.125
‐ Aw, aren't you cute?

10:07.125 --> 10:08.250
[grunts]

10:08.250 --> 10:09.667
Bye now.

10:10.083 --> 10:10.958
Ha!

10:11.458 --> 10:12.542
ITO: Haruka!

10:13.583 --> 10:14.583
‐ No!

10:17.625 --> 10:19.500
No, no, no! Ito‐san!

10:20.292 --> 10:24.250
[groaning]
‐ Oh my, such heroic passion,

10:24.625 --> 10:26.167
such futility.

10:26.167 --> 10:27.208
[grunts]

10:28.083 --> 10:30.042
[Monkey hoots, screeches]

10:30.042 --> 10:30.500
[Lady Bullseye snarls]

10:30.500 --> 10:31.542
[hooting mockingly]

10:31.542 --> 10:33.333
‐ Great, okay,
you got her attention.

10:33.333 --> 10:35.125
Can we run now, please?
[Monkey growls]

10:36.667 --> 10:37.667
[groans]

10:43.083 --> 10:44.750
[hooting]

10:45.333 --> 10:46.917
‐ If you stop now,

10:47.208 --> 10:48.625
I'll make it quick
and painless,

10:49.167 --> 10:49.958
I promise!

10:49.958 --> 10:51.667
‐ Nope. Don't believe her!
She's lying!

10:52.375 --> 10:54.792
Well, sometimes you misunderstand
people's intentions!

10:54.792 --> 10:56.667
[Monkey screeching]

10:57.750 --> 10:59.000
[grunting]

10:59.000 --> 11:00.333
[blades whooshing]

11:02.417 --> 11:06.375
♪

11:07.375 --> 11:09.042
[glass shatters]

11:10.792 --> 11:11.333
[girl screams]

11:12.500 --> 11:14.833
‐ Okay, hang right! Hang right here!
Right, right, right, no.

11:14.833 --> 11:16.417
[Monkey screeches]
I said right!

11:17.500 --> 11:19.250
[grunting]

11:24.833 --> 11:25.667
‐ Ah!

11:26.500 --> 11:28.167
[screeches]

11:28.167 --> 11:30.125
Are you kidding me?

11:30.125 --> 11:32.708
‐ Oh‐ho sick! I mean,
I taught you that, right?

11:32.708 --> 11:33.958
Dumb question!
Of course I did!

11:35.417 --> 11:38.875
♪

11:39.375 --> 11:41.042
[thudding]

11:41.875 --> 11:46.458
♪

11:54.958 --> 11:57.500
Ohh! That was
way too close, okay.

11:57.500 --> 11:59.083
[hooting]

11:59.083 --> 12:01.542
Hey, hey, listen, listen, I know
it was hard leaving Akiko back there,

12:01.542 --> 12:02.917
but you did the right thing.

12:02.917 --> 12:05.208
Alright? This psychopath is after you.

12:05.208 --> 12:06.917
And‐and when you have
something to lose,

12:06.917 --> 12:08.583
people will always target that.

12:08.583 --> 12:10.083
Trust me.
[Monkey growls]

12:10.083 --> 12:11.875
Also, what is with you today?

12:11.875 --> 12:14.583
'Cause I am missing that, uh,
the rhythm we usually have.

12:14.583 --> 12:17.250
You know? Like where I give you orders
and you follow them?

12:17.250 --> 12:19.875
I mean, 'cause, you know, right now
it‐it‐it's like you're doing

12:19.875 --> 12:22.250
the exact opposite
of everything I say.

12:22.250 --> 12:24.083
And it's starting
to hurt my feelings,

12:24.083 --> 12:25.333
[growls]
if I'm being honest.

12:25.333 --> 12:26.208
LADY BULLSEYE: Hey!

12:27.458 --> 12:29.750
You didn't think
this was over, did you?

12:29.750 --> 12:30.917
[engine revving, tires screeching]

12:30.917 --> 12:32.708
‐ Normally, I respect perseverance,

12:32.708 --> 12:35.083
but this is just
downright stalkerish.

12:38.042 --> 12:40.167
Holy shit!
[Lady Bullseye yells]

12:40.167 --> 12:42.458
[glass shatters]
[people screaming]

12:43.833 --> 12:45.042
[metallic grinding]

12:45.042 --> 12:47.500
[Monkey hoots]
Okay, okay, go for the wires!

12:48.375 --> 12:49.250
[hooting]

12:49.250 --> 12:51.125
No, not that way!

12:54.708 --> 12:58.000
Don't jump into her line of sight!
Are you kidding me?

13:00.042 --> 13:01.042
‐ Argh!
[glass shatters]

13:02.625 --> 13:03.292
[yells]

13:05.333 --> 13:06.625
‐ Hey, congrats!

13:06.625 --> 13:08.958
A hundred and fifty years
of bad luck, ya dipshit!

13:08.958 --> 13:13.333
[whining]
♪ circus music playing ♪

13:13.333 --> 13:15.083
MAN: [over radio]
Manzo. Where the hell are you?

13:15.083 --> 13:17.458
Those balloons were supposed
to be delivered two hours ago.

13:17.458 --> 13:19.292
You're ruining their birthday!

13:19.292 --> 13:20.167
‐ Yes, sir!

13:20.167 --> 13:23.583
I appreciate you giving me
this chance to start my life over.

13:23.583 --> 13:24.792
MAN: I don't care!

13:24.792 --> 13:26.375
Don't make me regret
hiring you.

13:26.375 --> 13:27.042
‐ Yes, sir!

13:34.250 --> 13:35.542
[screeching]

13:39.417 --> 13:40.583
[chuckles]

13:46.458 --> 13:47.500
[clanging]

13:47.500 --> 13:48.917
[tires screeching]

13:49.500 --> 13:50.250
[gasps]

13:52.458 --> 13:54.083
[screeching]

13:54.083 --> 13:57.083
‐ Don't you worry, sir!
You can always trust Ma‐‐

13:57.083 --> 14:00.375
[metallic crunching, grinding]

14:04.083 --> 14:05.083
‐ Argh!

14:07.167 --> 14:09.542
Ha ha! Ooh, oh shit!

14:10.958 --> 14:13.042
Son of a‐‐
[explosion booms]

14:22.042 --> 14:23.417
[distant sirens wailing]

14:23.417 --> 14:25.792
‐ Phew, I thought we lost you there.

14:25.792 --> 14:26.833
[chokes]

14:28.417 --> 14:29.917
‐ Please God, let me die.

14:29.917 --> 14:31.625
‐ Not today, my friend.

14:32.375 --> 14:33.583
Not today.

14:33.583 --> 14:34.333
[clattering]

14:34.833 --> 14:36.333
‐ Hey, over here!

14:36.333 --> 14:37.542
I found another one!

14:38.250 --> 14:39.417
Oh my god.

14:40.042 --> 14:41.875
‐ Do not touch me.

14:49.250 --> 14:50.083
[Ito groans]

14:50.083 --> 14:51.500
‐ No, no, no. Shh.

14:51.500 --> 14:52.792
Don't try to talk, Ito‐san.

14:53.208 --> 14:54.875
It's okay. It's okay.
[coughs]

14:55.625 --> 14:56.750
I'm right here.

14:57.667 --> 14:58.583
Hurry!

14:59.042 --> 15:01.750
[siren wailing]

15:08.750 --> 15:09.917
[meows]

15:11.417 --> 15:16.458
♪

15:19.208 --> 15:20.958
‐ Come on, buddy.
Come on. Get up.

15:21.333 --> 15:22.208
Get up.

15:22.750 --> 15:24.250
Hey, you gotta fight it, okay.

15:24.708 --> 15:27.042
Look, I‐I know I told you
I saw a light

15:27.042 --> 15:29.083
at the end of the tunnel
but the truth is,

15:29.458 --> 15:30.792
it was pitch black.

15:30.792 --> 15:31.958
Okay? Like I was, um,

15:32.375 --> 15:33.917
like I was floating
in nothingness. Okay?

15:33.917 --> 15:35.333
Then I saw your face,

15:35.750 --> 15:37.792
and so I reached out to you.

15:37.792 --> 15:39.875
And if you're there now,
you gotta fight it.

15:39.875 --> 15:40.833
Okay? Just come back.

15:42.250 --> 15:43.708
Look, I‐I know
I've been hard on you, man,

15:43.708 --> 15:44.833
but‐but the truth is,

15:45.792 --> 15:47.458
you're the only real friend
I've ever had,

15:47.458 --> 15:48.500
so if you can‐‐

15:49.250 --> 15:50.500
You just can't leave me here alone.

15:50.500 --> 15:52.000
Okay? Please. Please.

15:53.625 --> 15:55.000
[coughing]

15:55.000 --> 15:55.875
Oh, thank God.

15:56.917 --> 15:58.333
Are you okay?
[coughs]

15:58.667 --> 15:59.708
[grunts]

16:00.875 --> 16:01.750
Akiko?

16:02.208 --> 16:03.083
You‐‐

16:03.750 --> 16:05.750
Did you not hear what I‐‐

16:05.750 --> 16:07.250
Uh, yeah, no, she's fine.

16:07.250 --> 16:08.583
But I‐‐ I'm sure of it.

16:08.583 --> 16:10.583
No, There were sirens‐‐
[groans]

16:10.583 --> 16:13.917
Hey, hey, hey. Hey. Hey.
Where you going, bud?

16:14.458 --> 16:15.625
You're, like, half drowned.

16:15.625 --> 16:18.042
You wanna just take
a breather for a second?

16:19.625 --> 16:22.500
‐ Authorities are investigating
the monkey's involvement

16:22.500 --> 16:24.083
in the explosion earlier today

16:24.083 --> 16:26.292
at the home
of Councilor Yokohama's niece,

16:26.292 --> 16:27.458
Akiko Yokohama.

16:27.792 --> 16:30.250
Police have issued
a warning urging citizens

16:30.250 --> 16:31.958
to avoid contact
with the monkey

16:31.958 --> 16:34.208
and if sighted,
to call them immediately.

16:34.667 --> 16:36.000
‐ Oh God.

16:40.208 --> 16:42.750
The last time I was
in this hospital

16:42.750 --> 16:45.333
was to say goodbye
to your parents.

16:46.625 --> 16:49.417
I promised them
I would protect you,

16:50.000 --> 16:51.208
and now‐‐

16:52.042 --> 16:53.458
[sobs]

16:53.458 --> 16:54.958
I'm so sorry.

16:56.542 --> 16:59.167
Just tell me
how to fix this.

17:02.500 --> 17:03.542
Please.

17:04.208 --> 17:06.375
AKIKO:
You can re‐hire me.

17:06.375 --> 17:07.583
‐ Akiko.

17:08.292 --> 17:09.417
You're alright!

17:09.417 --> 17:10.583
‐ Seriously,

17:11.333 --> 17:13.583
you barely know
how to use your phone.

17:17.458 --> 17:20.333
‐ You'd have to take a pay cut.

17:20.333 --> 17:22.375
‐ [laughs weakly]
I was getting paid?

17:22.375 --> 17:25.375
‐ Excuse me, sir,
you are needed.

17:29.542 --> 17:33.417
♪

17:37.000 --> 17:40.583
♪

17:45.042 --> 17:46.417
[sobs]

17:46.708 --> 17:50.167
♪ somber music playing ♪

17:50.167 --> 17:53.083
♪

17:59.625 --> 18:02.167
‐ I know he might have seemed
like a slouch,

18:02.917 --> 18:04.583
but he was a good cop.

18:05.708 --> 18:07.458
Rest easy, old partner.

18:09.250 --> 18:10.208
‐ Partner?

18:11.792 --> 18:12.667
‐ Oh.

18:13.792 --> 18:14.708
He told you.

18:15.125 --> 18:19.000
♪

18:25.667 --> 18:26.625
Detective.

18:28.000 --> 18:28.958
Where are you going?

18:29.458 --> 18:32.333
♪

18:33.958 --> 18:34.542
[Haruka gasps]

18:34.958 --> 18:35.958
‐ Of course.

18:41.958 --> 18:45.667
♪

18:48.583 --> 18:49.667
[Monkey whines]

18:49.667 --> 18:52.333
♪

18:54.125 --> 18:55.167
[hoots]

18:56.417 --> 18:59.208
♪

18:59.208 --> 19:00.833
BRYCE: Hey, buddy, um,

19:00.833 --> 19:04.500
look, I don't want to cut this short,
but you're all over the news right now.

19:04.500 --> 19:06.375
You know?
We, uh, we just can't stay here.

19:06.375 --> 19:07.375
[Monkey whines]

19:08.417 --> 19:09.917
You know, if I had, uh,

19:09.917 --> 19:14.042
known that killing Takahara
would lead to all this, uh... death,

19:14.458 --> 19:17.625
I‐I... Well, I probably
wouldn't have taken the job.

19:20.500 --> 19:23.583
♪ dramatic music playing ♪

19:23.583 --> 19:27.167
♪

19:27.167 --> 19:31.208
[evil laughter]

19:32.250 --> 19:34.667
[roaring]

19:35.417 --> 19:38.250
Anyway, um...
man, I hate hospitals.

19:38.250 --> 19:40.375
You know? Like, I mean,
what is that smell?

19:40.375 --> 19:42.917
You know? It's like,
is somebody burning eggs or something?

19:42.917 --> 19:45.375
Like, even the lighting is nauseating.

19:46.500 --> 19:49.000
[clears throat]
You know, anyway, like I said, I, um,

19:49.583 --> 19:50.667
I wouldn't have taken the job.

19:50.667 --> 19:52.458
I mean, I'm‐I'm dead because of it,

19:52.458 --> 19:55.083
so, you know, really in many ways
I've suffered the most.

19:55.083 --> 19:56.083
It's, uh‐‐

19:56.750 --> 19:57.750
So, hey,

19:57.750 --> 19:58.542
what you think, huh?

19:58.542 --> 19:59.292
You hungry?

20:01.833 --> 20:03.333
[Monkey whimpers]

20:09.292 --> 20:11.667
I don't know about you, bud,
but I think we've earned ourselves

20:11.667 --> 20:13.292
a little R&R, huh?

20:13.292 --> 20:14.917
What should we do?
Where do we wanna go? Huh?

20:14.917 --> 20:18.125
Hey, you know, I know a beach
in Thailand where anything goes.

20:18.125 --> 20:19.708
Yeah?
[chuckles]

20:19.708 --> 20:21.042
You know? Or Macau.

20:21.042 --> 20:24.333
We could go to Macau.
Though I am banned from the Lisboa.

20:24.333 --> 20:26.250
That's a long story.
Fun story, but a long one.

20:26.250 --> 20:29.083
Oh! Hey! Goa's, you know, pretty fun
this time of year, too.

20:29.417 --> 20:32.208
Ain't nothing can't be cured
by margaritas, sunshine,

20:32.208 --> 20:33.417
and a few more margaritas!

20:33.417 --> 20:34.375
[chuckles]
You know?

20:34.375 --> 20:37.000
\What do you think, huh?
Are you a salt‐on‐the‐rim kinda monkey?

20:38.375 --> 20:39.625
MAN: [on TV]
This is absurd!

20:39.625 --> 20:41.708
We've completely lost
all rule of law!

20:41.708 --> 20:44.833
‐ You mean the rule of law
that only benefits the wealthy?

20:44.833 --> 20:46.042
‐ Oh, come on!

20:46.042 --> 20:48.917
I'm talking about a monkey
going on a killing spree!

20:48.917 --> 20:51.417
‐ Yeah, a monkey
that's cleaning up the corruption

20:51.417 --> 20:54.083
our government has sanctioned
for far too long!

20:54.083 --> 20:56.625
‐ Oh my god,
you can't be serious right now.

20:56.625 --> 20:57.917
‐ I‐I am serious!

20:58.250 --> 20:59.875
I'm not afraid
to tell the truth.

21:00.417 --> 21:01.458
BRYCE: Wow. Really? Okay.

21:01.458 --> 21:04.375
We survived this whole ordeal
and you want to risk your life again

21:04.375 --> 21:05.292
with a meal here?

21:05.292 --> 21:06.792
[laughs]

21:07.875 --> 21:08.583
[grunts]

21:08.583 --> 21:11.875
Oh, Akiko house‐broke you, huh?
[laughs]

21:11.875 --> 21:13.083
Glad I missed that part.

21:14.667 --> 21:16.792
Oh man. I love these things.

21:16.792 --> 21:18.583
You're in for a real treat, buddy.

21:18.583 --> 21:20.208
Your butthole's gonna get
a workout: see this button‐‐

21:20.208 --> 21:21.000
[grunts]

21:21.625 --> 21:23.083
What the‐‐ Dude?

21:23.083 --> 21:24.583
[hooting, screeching]

21:24.583 --> 21:26.375
Wha‐‐ A demon?

21:26.375 --> 21:27.750
No, no, no, no,
I'm not a demon!

21:27.750 --> 21:29.083
What the hell are you
talking about?

21:30.542 --> 21:32.292
I'm sorry, ruined your life?

21:32.292 --> 21:33.542
No. No, no, no, no.

21:33.542 --> 21:37.458
You think I asked to be turned into
some dumb‐ass monkey's ghost pet?

21:37.458 --> 21:39.083
[growls]

21:39.083 --> 21:40.417
Okay, I didn't mean that!
I didn't mean it.

21:40.417 --> 21:42.792
Okay, hey, come on, man.
Look how far we've come!

21:42.792 --> 21:44.250
I can fix this!

21:44.250 --> 21:45.792
Wait! wait, wait, wait, wait!

21:45.792 --> 21:47.167
[coughs]

21:47.583 --> 21:48.708
Come back!

21:49.250 --> 21:51.000
Monkey, I'm sorry!

21:51.500 --> 21:52.875
Monkey!

21:54.250 --> 21:58.125
♪ Fanel's Mén playing ♪

21:58.125 --> 22:01.625
♪

